Pacific Investment Management Co.,
which managed $1.97 trillion as of Sept. 30, says in an e-mailed
statement today.
*Quasi-sovereign utilities in emerging Asia have operational and
financial advantages and may offer a spread above corresponding
government debt: report
*The region’s “tremendous” scope for infrastructure
development, especially in electrification, may translate into
investment opportunities: report
*The amount of debt issued by Asian utilities has quadrupled to
$19b in the last five years: report
*Despite state support, underlying  cash flow  can be volatile and
credit fundamentals can weaken: report
*Tariff increases not keeping up with rising fuel costs can sap
